column168: ON DECEMBER 16, 1986 A DEL-MED, INC., DRIVER PARKED HIS FORD MAXI-VAN AT 17 04 DIAMOND STREET, PHILADELPHIA, PA. ON THE MORNING OF DECEMBER 17, 1986, T HE DRIVER DISCOVERED THAT FORCED ENTRY INTO THE VEHICLE HAD BEEN MADE AND T HAT 4 MOLYBDENUM-99/TECHNETIUM-99M GENERATORS HAD BEEN STOLEN. A REPORT WAS MADE TO THE PHILADELPHIA 22ND DISTRICT POLICE AND THE NATIONAL RESPONSE CE NTER. THE POLICE RECOVERED 3 OF THE 4 GENERATORS IN THE GENERAL VICINITY OF 1704 DIAMOND STREET. REPRESENTATIVES OF THE NUCLEAR REGULATORY COMMISSION AND THE DEPARTMENT OF HEALTH SURVEYED THE 3 PACKAGES. THEY DETERMINED THAT NO RADIOACTIVE MATERIAL HAD ESCAPED FROM THE 3 PACKAGES AND RELEASED THEM T O A MALLINCKRODT REPRESENTATIVE FOR RETURN TO THE MALLINCKRODT FACILITY IN FOLCROFT, PA. THE 1 MISSING RADIOACTIVE PACKAGE REMAINS UNACCOUNTED FOR TO DATE.
